# Clerk Billing & Feature Gating

This app uses [Clerk billing](https://clerk.com/docs/billing/b2c-saas) for subscriptions and payments. Gate premium functionality with **features** (preferred) or **plans**.

## Plans & Features

| Plan | Slug | Features |
|------|------|----------|
| Free | `free_user` | `3_deck_limit` |
| Pro | `pro` | `unlimited_decks`, `ai_flashcard_generation` |

Use these exact slugs in `has()`, `<Protect>`, and the Clerk Dashboard.

## Server — `has()` (preferred for Server Components & Server Actions)

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { has, userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

// Feature check (preferred)
const canUseAi = has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" });
const hasUnlimitedDecks = has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" });

// Plan check (when plan-level access is enough)
const isPro = has({ plan: "pro" });
```

Combine with [clerk-auth.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/clerk-auth.mdc) — always call `auth()` in Server Actions and enforce limits **server-side**, not only in the UI.

## Client — `<Protect>`

```tsx
import { Protect } from "@clerk/nextjs";

<Protect feature="ai_flashcard_generation" fallback={<UpgradePrompt />}>
  <AiGenerateButton />
</Protect>
```

## Pricing page — `<PricingTable />`

```tsx
import { PricingTable } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div className="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Enforcement Rules

1. **Prefer feature checks** — use `has({ feature: "..." })` over plan checks when gating specific capabilities.
2. **Enforce in Server Actions** — UI gating alone is not enough; validate before every mutation.
3. **Deck limit (free users)** — before creating a deck, if the user lacks `unlimited_decks`, count their decks and reject when they already have 3.
4. **AI generation (Pro only)** — require `ai_flashcard_generation` in the server action that generates cards.
5. **Upgrade UX** — when access is denied, show a clear upgrade path (link to pricing or `<PricingTable />`), not a generic error.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — only hides button in UI, no server check
<Button onClick={createDeck}>Create deck</Button>

// ✅ GOOD — enforce deck limit in Server Action
export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId, has } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  if (!has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" })) {
    const existing = await db
      .select()
      .from(decksTable)
      .where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));
    if (existing.length >= 3) {
      throw new Error("Free plan allows up to 3 decks. Upgrade to Pro for unlimited decks.");
    }
  }

  // ... create deck
}
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — protect Pro-only UI
<Protect feature="ai_flashcard_generation" fallback={<Link href="/pricing">Upgrade to Pro</Link>}>
  <GenerateWithAiButton deckId={deckId} />
</Protect>
```
